        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 2:34PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 234 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Newbern, or 8 miles southeast of Greensboro, moving northeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Selma, Brent, Valley Grande, Marion, Centreville, Greensboro,
Uniontown, Newbern, Faunsdale, Dayton, Vaiden, Parnell, Heiberger,
Lawley, Paul M Grist State Park, Talladega National Forest, Marion
Junction, Potter Station, Randolph, and Radford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
